SP.P:
I find I must impose upon him no farther, it may be dangerous.




AIR XXV. Geminiani's Minuet.

Cease to grieve thee, gentle Swain;

Love will soon reward thy Care;

Joy shall banish ev'ry Pain,

Since the Maid is kind as fair;

True and constant as the Dove,

That mourns the Absence of her Love.



Mr. Edgar, pray don't be so uneasy; I confess I have impos'd upon you; but you will excuse it when you know all: We Women do take such Pleasure in the little Anxieties we give you Men, that I cou'd not avoid it: but what I have done, and what I will do to serve you, shall make you ample Amends.
